source.name: RSS Feeds for Data Buoys
source.description: The National Weather Service (NWS) National Data Buoy Center uses RSS feeds to disseminate buoy station observations.  These RSS feeds are regularly updated to include: wind direction and speed; wind gusts; wave height; dominant wave period; average period; mean wave direction; atmospheric pressure; pressure tendency; air temperature; water temperature; dew point; visibility; and tide.
